race.description: Elders Rural Services Wagga Wagga Super Maiden Plate
race.comment: TASSY FOX (12) returned last time with a solid second over this track and trip. Has found the maiden win elusive but has improvement to come second-up and gets a great chance to finally break the ice. CENTRAL OTAGO (4) is a Calyx gelding out of Essence, who's the same dam as 2x Listed winner Indispensable. Has trialled well in readiness and is expected to play a major role. HE'S OUR BOY (2) found the line strongly last time out when third here. Cherry-ripe now so he is one of the prime contenders. JENNI DIVINE (9) was prominent at the corner and finished third last time here when resuming. Fitter and should give another bold sight.
